<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene fetlerii" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fetlerii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Silene fetlerii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a new addition to the Greek flora.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
This is a rare and local species, recently described from Bulgaria and thought to be confined to the serpentine substrates of only two localities, near the Villages of Fotinovo and Chichevo to the south (
<bibRefCitation author="Pavlova, D. K." journalOrPublisher="Annales Botanici Fennici" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="387 - 393" refId="B7669110" refString="Pavlova, D. K., 2014. Silene fetlerii (Caryophyllaceae), a new species from Bulgaria. Annales Botanici Fennici 51: 387 - 393" title="Silene fetlerii (Caryophyllaceae), a new species from Bulgaria" volume="51" year="2014">Pavlova 2014</bibRefCitation>
). Our Greek specimen (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStartId="F7677640" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">15</figureCitation>
) agrees with the description of the Bulgarian material in all essential characters: it has narrow linear leaves and lanceolate bracts, 6-9 mm long calyces, 5-6 mm long capsules included in calyx, a capsule/anthophore ratio of 1.3-2/1 and a rounded capsule base with a narrow and acute neck. We did not observe any viscid indumentum on the lower stem nodes in our specimen, a character usually found in the Bulgarian plants.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
This is another species that turns out to cross the political border between Bulgaria and Greece as the new locality lies ca. 12 km south of the border. The new locality expands the known 
<normalizedToken originalValue="species’">species'</normalizedToken>
distribution for ca. 25 km to the SW (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F7677586" captionText="Figure 11. Distribution map of Onosma kittanae, Aethionema saxatile subsp. rhodopaeum and Silene fetlerii in Greece and Bulgaria." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/656688" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">11</figureCitation>
). This single Greek population fits the Critically Endangered Category [B1ab(i ii iii iv) + 2ab(i ii iii iv)] (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN," journalOrPublisher="Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK: IUCN. iv + 32 pp" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668800" refString="IUCN, , 2012. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. Second edition. Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK: IUCN. iv + 32pp" title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. Second edition" year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
) and shares the same habitat characteristics with that described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pavlova, D. K." journalOrPublisher="Annales Botanici Fennici" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="387 - 393" refId="B7669110" refString="Pavlova, D. K., 2014. Silene fetlerii (Caryophyllaceae), a new species from Bulgaria. Annales Botanici Fennici 51: 387 - 393" title="Silene fetlerii (Caryophyllaceae), a new species from Bulgaria" volume="51" year="2014">Pavlova (2014)</bibRefCitation>
; even some rare, range-restricted serpentine taxa that accompany 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene fetlerii" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fetlerii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Silene fetlerii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Bulgaria (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Constantinidis, Kougioumoutzis &amp; Kalpoutzakis" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="D. K. Pavlova" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Aethionema" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aethionema saxatile subsp. rhodopaeum" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="saxatile" subSpecies="rhodopaeum">Aethionema saxatile subsp. rhodopaeum</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Onosma" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Onosma kittanae" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kittanae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Onosma kittanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see under these taxa) are also found in Greece. The identity of the 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene spergulifolia" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spergulifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Silene spergulifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collections from Nomos Evrou needs further investigation.
</paragraph>
